# Walker Architecture

The walker package handles directory traversal and file selection logic.

## Core Components

- [walker.go](mdc:walker/walker.go): Main walker implementation for traversing directories
- [gitignore.go](mdc:walker/gitignore.go): Implements .gitignore file parsing and pattern matching
- [git_validation.go](mdc:walker/git_validation.go): Validates if directory is a git repository
- [processor_integration.go](mdc:walker/processor_integration.go): Integrates processors with the walker

## Features

- Respects nested .gitignore files
- Skips common directories and files by default (node_modules, .git, etc.)
- Git repository validation to prevent accidental modification of non-versioned files
